/*- -*- C++ -*- -------------------------------------------------------------*\

History after the 2) written in gmsh2ToFoam.C:

    3) Now supports version 2.0 of the .msh file format. Instead of
    silently ignoring unhandled element types gmsh2ToFoam now produces
    an error. (16/Feb/2007 Takuya OSHIMA <oshima@eng.niigata-u.ac.jp>)

    4) Improved compatibility with .msh files generated by Windows versions of
    Gmsh. (17/Feb/2007 Takuya OSHIMA <oshima@eng.niigata-u.ac.jp>)

    5) Incorporated primitivePatch::meshPointMap() call optimization
    from Davidh's gmshToFoamMod. Quotation from gmshToFoamMod.C:

      primitivePatch::meshPointMap() call was moved outside of
      findFace() instead const Map<label> meshPointMap is passed as an
      argument.  This was done so that the
      primitivePatch::meshPointMap() call could be moved outside the
      loop which was going over all the "faces" of all the "patches"
      in the domain.  This should improve the conversion speed.

    (18/Feb/2007 Takuya OSHIMA <oshima@eng.niigata-u.ac.jp>)

    6) Fixed correspondence between OpenFOAM cellZone/patch numbering
    and Gmsh physical/elementary entity tagging. The meaning of
    physical entity tag seems to be different between .msh file format
    versions.  (18/Feb/2007 Takuya OSHIMA
    <oshima@eng.niigata-u.ac.jp>)

    7) Use physical region names (string labels) instead of names
    automatically assigned by gmsh2ToFoam (such as "patch0") for
    patch, cellZones and faceZones if $PhysicalNames section is
    present in the .msh file. (19/Feb/2007 Takuya OSHIMA
    <oshima@eng.niigata-u.ac.jp>)

    8) Following one of the Gmsh authors' suggestion, another
    modification is made to physical/elementary region (entity) number
    handling. See http://www.geuz.org/pipermail/gmsh/2007/002395.html
    for details. (1/Mar/2007 Takuya OSHIMA
    <oshima@eng.niigata-u.ac.jp>)

    9) Automatically generated patches/cellZones names ("patch1," ...)
    are now labeled by numbers based on original region numbers given
    in a .geo file, instead of the order of their appearence in a .msh
    file. (5/Mar/2007 Takuya OSHIMA <oshima@eng.niigata-u.ac.jp>)

    10) Deletes the defaultFaces patch if its size is finally
    determined to be zero. (5/Mar/2007 Takuya OSHIMA
    <oshima@eng.niigata-u.ac.jp>)

    11) Removal of unreferred points. (5/Mar/2007 Takuya OSHIMA
    <oshima@eng.niigata-u.ac.jp>)

    12) RenumberMesh matrix bandwidth compression with
    cell/face-Zone/Set handling. (11/Mar/2007 Takuya OSHIMA
    <oshima@eng.niigata-u.ac.jp>)

    13) Deletes zero-sized patches (internal faceZones). This is an enhancement
    to 10) above. (11/Mar/2007 Takuya OSHIMA
    <oshima@eng.niigata-u.ac.jp>)

    14) Base patch types can be defined by the second word of the
    string labels. (12/Mar/2007 Takuya OSHIMA <oshima@eng.niigata-u.ac.jp>)

    15) Completely overhauled and refactored the code for
        readability. (25/Mar/2007 Takuya OSHIMA
        <oshima@eng.niigata-u.ac.jp>)

    16) Fixed a faceZone naming bug. (26/Mar/2007 Takuya OSHIMA
        <oshima@eng.niigata-u.ac.jp>)

    17) Refined text message outputs for both of the
        verbose/non-verbose modes. (26/Mar/2007 Takuya OSHIMA
        <oshima@eng.niigata-u.ac.jp>)

    18) Added simplified checkMesh test capability (by simply calling
        polyMesh::checkMesh()). (26/Mar/2007 Takuya OSHIMA
        <oshima@eng.niigata-u.ac.jp>)

    19) Run Gmsh automatically when a .geo file is
        specified. (26/Mar/2007 Takuya OSHIMA
        <oshima@eng.niigata-u.ac.jp>)

    20) Splitted the code to libgmshFoam and gmsh2ToFoam so that the
        library part can be integrated into the I/O layer of Gmsh
        itself. (28/Mar/2007 Takuya OSHIMA
        <oshima@eng.niigata-u.ac.jp>)

    21) Reduced FatalErrorIn calls and issues Warnings instead where
        possible, to avoid Gmsh crash. (28/Mar/2007 Takuya OSHIMA
        <oshima@eng.niigata-u.ac.jp>)

    22) Eleminated use of the argList class from libgmshFoam for
        reducing verbosity. (29/Mar/2007 Takuya OSHIMA
        <oshima@eng.niigata-u.ac.jp>)

    23) Created libgmshMessage for making it possible to share
    text message lines between OpenFOAM applications and Gmsh by
    separately implimenting the stream writer function endl() for the
    message stream. (29/Mar/2007 Takuya OSHIMA
    <oshima@eng.niigata-u.ac.jp>)

    24) Verbosity control all over the code following the gmsh
    verbosity (which has the default verbosity of 3). (31/Mar/2007
    Takuya OSHIMA <oshima@eng.niigata-u.ac.jp>)

    25) Created foamToGmsh. (31/Mar/2007 Takuya OSHIMA
    <oshima@eng.niigata-u.ac.jp>)

    26) Suppression of the OpenFOAM banner for Gmsh with libgmshFoam.
    (02/Apr/2007 Takuya OSHIMA <oshima@eng.niigata-u.ac.jp>)

    27) Implemented the interface code to libgmshFoam postprocessing
    module into Gmsh. (02/Apr/2007 Takuya OSHIMA
    <oshima@eng.niigata-u.ac.jp>)

    28) Implemented mesh point motion into postprocessing views via
    the GeneralizedRaise feature. (07/Apr/2007 Takuya OSHIMA
    <oshima@eng.niigata-u.ac.jp>)

    29) Support for the Cygwin versions of Gmsh. (08/Apr/2007 Takuya
    OSHIMA <oshima@eng.niigata-u.ac.jp>)

    30) Created the gmshFoam script. (08/Apr/2007 Takuya OSHIMA
    <oshima@eng.niigata-u.ac.jp>)

    31) Problem fixed that Gmsh crashes when a detected field is not
    present at a later time instant. (09/Apr/2007 Takuya OSHIMA
    <oshima@eng.niigata-u.ac.jp>)

    32) vol/surfaceTensor fields support. (09/Apr/2007 Takuya OSHIMA
    <oshima@eng.niigata-u.ac.jp>)

    33) Implemented a simple realtime monitoring capability of
    computation progress through Gmsh solver selection capability:
    gmshFoamMonitor. (10/Apr/2007 Takuya OSHIMA
    <oshima@eng.niigata-u.ac.jp>)

    34) Added option handling capability through dictionary to
    gmshFoamMonitor. (11/Apr/2007 Takuya OSHIMA
    <oshima@eng.niigata-u.ac.jp>)

    35) Fixed mesh motion handling bugs. (11/Apr/2007 Takuya OSHIMA
    <oshima@eng.niigata-u.ac.jp>)

\*---------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
